      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## Highlights\n\n**Copy from the file explorer now works.** Right-clicking any Markdown file in the file explorer (or using the three-dot menu) copies *that* file — even if it isn't open. Previously this silently copied the active note or failed with \"No active Markdown file.\"\n\n**Image embeds are fixed.** `![[image.png]]`, `![[image.png|300]]`, and `![[image.png|caption]]` now produce properly embedded base64 images. Previously they could be destroyed during conversion or lose their `src` entirely.\n\n**Code blocks are left alone.** Text inside code fences and inline code spans is no longer touched by highlight/math/task-list/callout conversion — `$PATH` in a bash snippet stays `$PATH`.\n\n**Medium footnotes work again.** Standard `[^1]` footnotes convert to superscript references with a clean \"Notes\" section (no dead anchors or ↩ back-links).\n\n## Fixes\n\n- Pipe-aliased embeds (`![[note|alias]]`) now resolve like Obsidian does\n- Consecutive callouts render as separate blockquotes\n- Image filenames containing `&` resolve correctly; captions with `&`/quotes render correctly\n- Exact block-ID matching for `![[note#^id]]` embeds\n- CRLF (Windows) notes convert correctly end-to-end\n- Plain-text clipboard entry no longer double-decodes entities; emoji survive\n- Fixed quadratic regex backtracking on pathological input (12× faster, no more UI hangs)\n\n## Internals\n\n- All dependencies updated (vitest 4, ESLint 10, TypeScript 6, KaTeX 0.17); `npm audit` clean\n- Node 24 LTS toolchain; CI actions updated\n- Release assets now ship with GitHub build provenance attestation\n- Test suite grown from 146 to 293 tests, plus 67 end-to-end CLI tests against a live vault\n\n**Full Changelog**: https://github.com/canartuc/pubcopy/compare/1.3.3...1.4.0\n",
