      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's New in 1.2.0\n\n### New Feature: Copy as Markdown\n\nThird copy command alongside \"Copy for Medium\" and \"Copy for Substack\". Outputs clean markdown with Obsidian-specific syntax stripped:\n\n- Frontmatter, tags, wikilinks, comments, block IDs removed\n- Embeds resolved and inlined\n- Standard markdown preserved as-is (no HTML conversion)\n\nAvailable in Command Palette, right-click submenu, and three-dot menu.\n\n```\nPubcopy\n├── Copy for Medium      (platform-optimized HTML)\n├── Copy for Substack    (platform-optimized HTML)\n└── Copy as Markdown     (clean markdown, new)\n```\n\n### Architecture\n\n- Added `outputMode: \"html\" | \"markdown\"` discriminator to `PlatformProfile` interface\n- Markdown profile triggers early return in conversion pipeline (skips HTML stages)\n- 70 tests passing\n\n### Full Changelog\n\n**[1.1.0...1.2.0](https://github.com/canartuc/pubcopy/compare/1.1.0...1.2.0)**",
